thread.title: Volleyball: Catholic coasts in straight sets, wins region - PrepXtra
thread.title_full: Volleyball: Catholic coasts in straight sets, wins region - PrepXtra Story

author: News Sentinel staff
title: Volleyball: Catholic coasts in straight sets, wins region - PrepXtra
text:
Catholic High School's volleyball team continued its march toward the state tournament on Tuesday by coasting through the Region 2-AA bracket.
The Lady Irish, who advanced to state last year, eliminated Carter 25-20, 25-13, 25-17 in the semifinals before cruising past reigning state champion Christian Academy of Knoxville 25-18, 25-15, 25-16 in the finals at Rocky Top Sports World in Gatlinburg.
Kamila Cieslik had 16 kills and 13 digs for Catholic in the decisive match, and Olivia Kozemko added 27 assists.
Cieslik had 14 kills in the semifinals, and Margaret McCarty posted 12 points.
Catholic and CAK both advance to Thursday's state sectional round.
The Lady Irish will play host to Region 1-AA runner-up Elizabethton at 7 p.m. CAK will travel to play Sullivan South.
Region 1-AAA
Tennessee High def. Morristown West 25-8, 25-15, 25-18: Jasmine Williams posted nine blocks, but it wasn't enough to propel the Lady Trojans to a region title.
Morristown West, which beat Science Hill in the semifinals, advances to Thursday's 7 p.m. state sectional at Farragut.
Morristown West's Claire McDonald totaled 25 kills between the two matches to eclipse 2,000 for her career.
Region 2-A
Concord Christian def. Grace Christian 25-12, 25-20, 25-9: Allie Koepfer earned region tournament MVP honors as the Lady Lions cruised in straight sets, first against Coalfield 25-9, 25-6, 25-7 in the semifinals and then against Grace Christian for the championship.
Koepfer finished with seven kills, four digs and four aces in the final. Sindey Sherrill posted 11 kills. Concord will play host to Region 1-A runner-up Berean Christian in Thursday's sectional match. Grace Christian will travel to play South Greene.
